1
00:00:01,196 --> 00:00:05,246
After all the commotion
over the calico cat Taii's owner...

2
00:00:05,414 --> 00:00:08,545
we learned the real owner
was a man named Masuko.

3
00:00:08,628 --> 00:00:10,507
But when we went to visit Taii there...

4
00:00:13,472 --> 00:00:15,517
(cat meowing)

5
00:00:15,601 --> 00:00:17,605
Huh? What's with this cat?

6
00:00:17,897 --> 00:00:19,776
Mister, is something wrong?

7
00:00:19,859 --> 00:00:21,946
Oh, no, it's this cat.

8
00:00:22,030 --> 00:00:25,329
It doesn't look hurt or anything,
but there's blood on its paw...

9
00:00:25,871 --> 00:00:28,335
Wait... that means... could Masuko-san...

10
00:00:30,004 --> 00:00:31,006
No way...

11
00:00:35,516 --> 00:00:37,353
A refreshing autumn breeze blows through

12
00:00:37,436 --> 00:00:39,022
the gaiety of summer for a stylish and dashing display
of deduction.

13
00:00:39,106 --> 00:00:42,738
The Detective Boys and a locked room trick...
what's the secret of the cute calico cat?

14
00:00:42,822 --> 00:00:44,282
Seeing through the one and only truth.

15
00:00:44,367 --> 00:00:46,036
Looks like a kid, mind of an adult.

16
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:48,792
His name is Detective Conan!

17
00:00:48,875 --> 00:00:54,219
♪~

18
00:02:22,354 --> 00:02:28,366
~♪

19
00:02:32,369 --> 00:02:37,369
"Lucky Calico Cat Case (Part 2)"

20
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:40,565
Masuko-san, if you're okay, please answer!

21
00:02:41,025 --> 00:02:43,529
Masuko-san!
B... boy...

22
00:02:43,904 --> 00:02:46,577
Maybe he's just sleeping.

23
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:49,082
And the door lock is on, too.

24
00:02:49,166 --> 00:02:52,589
But the neighbor heard
a strange sound, right?

25
00:02:52,672 --> 00:02:56,764
Y... yeah, a loud sound,
like something crashing...

26
00:02:58,768 --> 00:03:02,859
And there's blood on the paw
of Masuko-san's cat.

27
00:03:02,942 --> 00:03:04,446
Something happened in there.

28
00:03:05,114 --> 00:03:08,204
- Haibara, call an ambulance.
- Got it.

29
00:03:08,537 --> 00:03:09,539
You guys...

30
00:03:09,623 --> 00:03:11,460
- Do you have any string?
- Huh?

31
00:03:11,752 --> 00:03:14,216
And tape, or wire?

32
00:03:15,051 --> 00:03:16,470
I've got some yarn.

33
00:03:16,929 --> 00:03:19,017
I've got bandages.

34
00:03:19,434 --> 00:03:21,021
I have paper clips.

35
00:03:21,355 --> 00:03:24,694
But what are you going to do
with stuff like this?

36
00:03:24,778 --> 00:03:26,532
I'm going to open this door lock.

37
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:30,790
First, tie the string to the
U-shaped bar of the door lock.

38
00:03:31,834 --> 00:03:35,800
Fix the knot to the tip of the bar
with a bandage.

39
00:03:36,426 --> 00:03:39,683
Run the string through the clip,
and the clip...

40
00:03:39,766 --> 00:03:42,981
fix it to the inside of the door,
and we're all set.

41
00:03:43,649 --> 00:03:47,991
Then just close the door
and pull the string hard...

42
00:03:48,409 --> 00:03:50,079
Ah... it opened.

43
00:03:50,955 --> 00:03:52,876
Where's the neighbor's room?

44
00:03:52,959 --> 00:03:54,296
R... right there...

45
00:03:54,921 --> 00:03:58,637
Then the closest one to next door,
left when you enter.

45
00:03:59,031 --> 00:04:00,157
Ugh... Oi, Conan!

46
00:04:00,516 --> 00:04:01,894
The back room, huh?

47 
00:04:06,987 --> 00:04:09,075
- An accident.
- Yeah.

48
00:04:09,868 --> 00:04:13,876
He stood a chair on the bed
to change the fluorescent light,

49
00:04:13,959 --> 00:04:16,840
lost his balance, and bashed
his head on the side table.

50
00:04:17,342 --> 00:04:20,556
I do it sometimes too,
but standing on a bed...

51
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:22,769
it's unstable and dangerous.

52
00:04:22,852 --> 00:04:26,026
Oh, please don't do things like that.

53
00:04:26,109 --> 00:04:30,368
Your mattress is high-end
and super fluffy, Sato-san.

54
00:04:30,826 --> 00:04:34,542
How do you know about
Detective Sato's bed?

55
00:04:34,626 --> 00:04:38,384
Have you slept in it?
Ah... no...

56
00:04:38,759 --> 00:04:42,016
Ayumi wants to sleep over
at Detective Sato's place too!

57
00:04:42,475 --> 00:04:47,443
Never mind that nonsense, what about
the condition of this room's owner?

58
00:04:47,527 --> 00:04:52,287
Ah... the surgery's done, but
he's apparently in critical, unconscious condition.

59
00:04:52,662 --> 00:04:56,044
Well, when he comes to, he'll be grateful.

60
00:04:56,128 --> 00:04:59,426
Thanks to Conan-kun opening
the door lock so quickly,

61
00:04:59,509 --> 00:05:02,807
- he was saved.
- No, before that...

62
00:05:03,350 --> 00:05:06,648
when he wakes up,
I think he'll tell us...

63
00:05:06,732 --> 00:05:09,237
who it was that attacked him.

64
00:05:09,487 --> 00:05:11,325
A... attacked?

65
00:05:11,408 --> 00:05:13,787
W... wasn't this an accident?

66
00:05:14,122 --> 00:05:17,670
Look, the chair is sitting on the comforter.

67
00:05:17,754 --> 00:05:22,138
If you were standing a chair on the bed,
wouldn't you pull the blanket back first?

68
00:05:22,805 --> 00:05:27,648
And look, Masuko-san still has
one slipper on.

69
00:05:27,815 --> 00:05:31,531
If you were climbing on a bed or chair,
wouldn't you take your slippers off?

70
00:05:31,865 --> 00:05:33,410
Th... that's right.

71
00:05:33,952 --> 00:05:36,833
And what's broken on the floor...

72
00:05:36,917 --> 00:05:40,508
I figured it was the old fluorescent
light he took out to replace,

73
00:05:41,218 --> 00:05:45,434
but the ends aren't darkened at all.
Like it's brand new.

74
00:05:46,103 --> 00:05:48,273
Which means...

75
00:05:48,357 --> 00:05:52,573
someone shoved Masuko-san in this bedroom,
gravely injuring him,

76
00:05:52,782 --> 00:05:55,454
then staged it to look like an accident.

77
00:05:56,039 --> 00:05:58,627
The neighbor heard a suspicious sound,

78
00:05:58,710 --> 00:06:01,091
and apparently it took nearly an hour...

79
00:06:01,174 --> 00:06:03,470
for the building manager to arrive,

80
00:06:03,762 --> 00:06:07,061
so there was plenty of time
to set up the trick.

81
00:06:07,145 --> 00:06:12,572
B... but there's apparently
only one spare key,

82
00:06:12,655 --> 00:06:15,911
and both keys were sitting
on the shelf in the living room.

83
00:06:16,121 --> 00:06:19,419
And the front door lock,
how would they even...

84
00:06:19,502 --> 00:06:21,423
That's already been solved.

85
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:23,635
Right, Conan-kun?

86
00:06:23,719 --> 00:06:27,018
If you can undo a door lock from outside,
locking it would be...

87
00:06:27,310 --> 00:06:30,232
Ah, no, I haven't gotten that far yet...

88
00:06:30,316 --> 00:06:31,526
Hey, look at this.

89
00:06:31,610 --> 00:06:34,449
- Something's on here.
- It's true.

90
00:06:37,955 --> 00:06:40,628
Hey, you kids, what are you
doing without permission...

91
00:06:40,711 --> 00:06:41,922
It's the intercom.

92
00:06:42,507 --> 00:06:43,967
The intercom here...

93
00:06:43,969 --> 00:06:49,119
records footage of whoever rings
the bell at the first-floor entrance.

94
00:06:50,022 --> 00:06:55,199
There you go. In the hour before we arrived,
there were three people.

95
00:06:55,866 --> 00:07:00,167
The audio's recorded too, and they
even said their names,

96
00:07:00,251 --> 00:07:03,966
so if we cross-check with the address book,
we should figure out who's who.

97
00:07:04,551 --> 00:07:06,638
There's no time for the
two of you to be flirting...

98
00:07:04,469 --> 00:07:08,569
- None at all.
- Wha...

99
00:07:08,569 --> 00:07:11,269
Geez, this is all because
Takagi-kun said something unnecessary.

100
00:07:11,106 --> 00:07:12,608
S... sorry.

101
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:16,700
Wrapping paper on the table,
and an old-ish carrier bag.

102
00:07:17,660 --> 00:07:21,459
So he really was trying to give
that calico cat to someone as a gift.

103
00:07:22,503 --> 00:07:25,050
There's tape and creases
on the wrapping paper,

104
00:07:25,134 --> 00:07:27,930
and torn marks here and there,
which means...

105
00:07:28,140 --> 00:07:31,271
did someone open it
once after it was wrapped?

106
00:07:31,479 --> 00:07:34,777
Hm? There's tape and scissors,
but...

107
00:07:36,364 --> 00:07:39,329
And the trash can nearby is empty too.

108
00:07:39,412 --> 00:07:41,958
Why isn't it here? That thing.

109
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:45,966
We found them pretty quickly.

110
00:07:46,509 --> 00:07:48,805
The three people on the intercom.

111
00:07:48,889 --> 00:07:52,938
Yeah, but the only one let into
the victim's room...

112
00:07:53,023 --> 00:07:57,907
was the first one. The second one
was dealt with at the entrance,

113
00:07:57,990 --> 00:08:01,999
and the third one rang the bell
at the front door,

114
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:05,214
but says they left when
there was no answer.

115
00:08:05,589 --> 00:08:09,472
All three are suspicious, aren't they?
That's right.

116
00:08:09,931 --> 00:08:13,772
If the second person came while
the first was still visiting,

117
00:08:14,065 --> 00:08:18,365
then after the second left,
the first could've done it too...

118
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:21,371
Come to think of it,
when you kids rang...

119
00:08:21,454 --> 00:08:24,293
the intercom at the entrance,
where was Masuko-san?

120
00:08:24,377 --> 00:08:26,381
We didn't ring anything.

121
00:08:26,715 --> 00:08:30,848
We were going to, but a resident
was just heading out,

122
00:08:30,931 --> 00:08:33,520
so we slipped in
when the door opened.

123
00:08:33,603 --> 00:08:36,276
We wanted to surprise him
by showing up suddenly.

124
00:08:36,359 --> 00:08:38,697
And we had an appointment.

125
00:08:38,780 --> 00:08:40,909
And we knew the room number.

126
00:08:41,161 --> 00:08:42,913
I... I see.

127
00:08:45,252 --> 00:08:47,423
Yes, I did meet with Masuko-san today.
- Furuyo Tsuyuguchi (41), Snack Bar Hostess

128
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:52,183
He treated me to some
tea in the living room.

129
00:08:52,808 --> 00:08:57,318
It was the length of one record...
so I was there about ten minutes.

130
00:08:57,401 --> 00:09:00,491
A record?
Yes, I...

131
00:09:00,574 --> 00:09:03,705
collect vintage jazz records.

132
00:09:04,123 --> 00:09:08,673
Masuko-san told me he'd found
a record I'd been searching for,

133
00:09:09,217 --> 00:09:13,308
so while I was there to pick it up,
he let me listen to one track.

134
00:09:13,558 --> 00:09:16,981
Did the doorbell ring
while you were there?

135
00:09:17,066 --> 00:09:20,322
I wouldn't know,
I was listening with headphones.

136
00:09:20,739 --> 00:09:23,787
Oh, sorry, could I borrow
your bathroom for a moment?

137
00:09:24,163 --> 00:09:27,169
Yes, of course.
Then, excuse me...

138
00:09:28,588 --> 00:09:30,300
Shoo, shoo.
Huh?

139
00:09:33,515 --> 00:09:35,644
(water running)

140
00:09:41,781 --> 00:09:43,076
Hey, boy.

141
00:09:43,159 --> 00:09:45,999
Why don't you turn off the light
when you're done?

142
00:09:46,165 --> 00:09:47,793
Whoa, sorry.

143
00:09:48,044 --> 00:09:52,219
Oh, I can't stand wastefulness,
so I just...

144
00:09:52,303 --> 00:09:53,930
(laughs)

145
00:09:54,348 --> 00:09:56,019
Like I said earlier...

146
00:09:56,102 --> 00:09:58,440
I only spoke with him
at the entrance.

147
00:09:58,773 --> 00:10:01,070
I didn't go inside the room.
- Mari Aso (28), former employee of Masuko.

148
00:10:01,154 --> 00:10:03,783
I didn't have an appointment,
and it seemed like he had...

149
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:05,495
a guest over.

150
00:10:05,954 --> 00:10:08,168
What was your business
with Masuko-san?

151
00:10:08,251 --> 00:10:13,136
Actually, I got fired from
President Masuko's company,

152
00:10:13,428 --> 00:10:15,974
so I came to say
a final goodbye to him.

153
00:10:16,059 --> 00:10:18,521
Don't tell me you came
to complain?

154
00:10:18,605 --> 00:10:20,609
No, the opposite.

155
00:10:20,692 --> 00:10:23,823
Getting fired was because of
a huge blunder of mine,

156
00:10:24,367 --> 00:10:25,953
and on top of that,
the president...

157
00:10:26,037 --> 00:10:29,168
arranged a new job for me,

158
00:10:29,251 --> 00:10:30,754
so I came partly to thank him...

159
00:10:30,837 --> 00:10:32,341
(cat meowing)
Hm?

160
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:36,015
Oh, what a cute kitty.
Can I hold it?

161
00:10:36,391 --> 00:10:37,393
Sure.

162
00:10:38,895 --> 00:10:40,148
So cute.

163
00:10:40,232 --> 00:10:42,778
Dai-chan's wagging his tail.
He's happy.

164
00:10:42,861 --> 00:10:44,365
Oh, you're right.
(cat meowing)

165
00:10:44,824 --> 00:10:47,246
Don't you have any
cats of your own?

166
00:10:47,579 --> 00:10:52,798
No, my parents hate animals,
even though I love them.

167
00:10:53,174 --> 00:10:55,262
Don't make me say it again.

168
00:10:55,679 --> 00:10:58,893
Yes, I did come as far as the front door,
- Rinpei Urushiya (53), novelist.

169
00:10:58,977 --> 00:11:00,772
but no matter how many
times I pressed the bell,

170
00:11:00,856 --> 00:11:05,073
he didn't answer,
so I gave up and went home.

171
00:11:05,490 --> 00:11:08,038
Then how did you get
inside the building?

172
00:11:08,121 --> 00:11:10,876
When I pressed the intercom
at the first-floor entrance,

173
00:11:10,959 --> 00:11:12,212
someone buzzed me in.

174
00:11:12,713 --> 00:11:16,763
There was no voice, so I can't say
for sure if it was him who opened it.

175
00:11:16,846 --> 00:11:19,602
What's your relationship
with Masuko-san?

176
00:11:20,062 --> 00:11:22,941
We've known each other
since our university days.

177
00:11:23,151 --> 00:11:26,074
We're writers who debuted
the same year.

178
00:11:26,157 --> 00:11:29,163
Though his novels didn't
sell at all,

179
00:11:29,246 --> 00:11:31,626
and it seems he gave up
on it early on.

180
00:11:32,127 --> 00:11:35,509
That said, for me too,
only my first work sold...

181
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:40,143
Looking back, maybe he made
the right call switching careers.

182
00:11:40,519 --> 00:11:42,272
So why did you come here?

183
00:11:42,356 --> 00:11:44,860
To brainstorm novel ideas
together.

184
00:11:45,237 --> 00:11:49,370
Whenever I got stuck, he'd often
help me out, like he always did.

185
00:11:49,620 --> 00:11:51,833
(cat meowing)
Hm...

186
00:11:52,417 --> 00:11:55,632
Get that cat away from me.
It's annoying.

187
00:11:55,715 --> 00:11:57,594
Mister, do you hate cats?

188
00:11:58,012 --> 00:12:01,853
Yeah, a stray scratched me
this morning too.

189
00:12:02,187 --> 00:12:05,610
I've got a bandage right here.
Ah.

190
00:12:07,948 --> 00:12:08,950
No need to worry.

191
00:12:09,451 --> 00:12:10,829
I've already treated it.

192
00:12:11,205 --> 00:12:12,624
Thanks.

193
00:12:12,875 --> 00:12:15,547
Well, if this cat were a great
detective like in that novel,

194
00:12:15,839 --> 00:12:18,553
that'd be a different story.

195
00:12:21,434 --> 00:12:22,853
Hmm.

196
00:12:23,062 --> 00:12:24,815
The order they rang
the intercom...

197
00:12:24,899 --> 00:12:29,450
Tsuyuguchi-san, Asou-san, then
Urushiya-san, that part checks out,

198
00:12:30,076 --> 00:12:32,789
but the time the neighbor
heard the suspicious sound...

199
00:12:32,873 --> 00:12:35,962
is too vague, so we can't
narrow it down to one person.

200
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:40,931
Looks like we'll just have to wait
for Masuko-san to regain consciousness.

201
00:12:41,015 --> 00:12:43,895
No, we won't even
need to wait for that.

202
00:12:44,313 --> 00:12:46,317
Huh?
Look...

203
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,029
Hm? Hah.

204
00:12:50,116 --> 00:12:52,329
That's the face of a little prankster.

205
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:04,386
So then?

206
00:13:04,469 --> 00:13:07,767
Around the time the neighbor
heard the suspicious sound,

207
00:13:08,017 --> 00:13:11,442
those three were the ones who
came to the victim's place?

208
00:13:11,650 --> 00:13:13,904
Yes.
But still...

209
00:13:14,281 --> 00:13:18,497
the front door had both the key
lock and the door lock on, right?

210
00:13:18,581 --> 00:13:20,460
Is this really a crime?

211
00:13:20,710 --> 00:13:26,472
Ah... yes. C... Conan-kun said
the scene wasn't an accident...

212
00:13:26,555 --> 00:13:29,311
And is this Conan-kun
in the room?

213
00:13:29,644 --> 00:13:32,609
No, he said he had
some shopping to do...

214
00:13:32,692 --> 00:13:33,986
I'm back.

215
00:13:34,905 --> 00:13:38,162
Conan-kun, what did you buy?

216
00:13:38,245 --> 00:13:41,460
The thing that was missing
from Masuko-san's room.

217
00:13:41,543 --> 00:13:42,962
The missing thing?

218
00:13:43,297 --> 00:13:44,925
This is it.

219
00:13:45,008 --> 00:13:46,720
Wrapping ribbon.

220
00:13:46,803 --> 00:13:49,141
When you tie a ribbon,
you cut the leftover ends...

221
00:13:49,226 --> 00:13:51,813
with scissors to make
them even.

222
00:13:51,897 --> 00:13:55,488
The fact that there were no ribbon
scraps in the trash can means...

223
00:13:55,613 --> 00:13:57,408
even though scissors
were prepared,

224
00:13:57,492 --> 00:14:00,206
maybe the length just
happened to be perfect?

225
00:14:00,915 --> 00:14:03,546
The contents were a used carrier bag,

226
00:14:03,629 --> 00:14:06,176
and there was tape too,
so it wasn't from a store...

227
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:09,139
It was something Masuko-san
wrapped himself.

228
00:14:09,224 --> 00:14:12,897
B... but what does
that have to do with anything?

229
00:14:13,357 --> 00:14:16,697
Are you half asleep? The fact that
it disappeared from the scene...

230
00:14:16,780 --> 00:14:19,411
means the culprit obviously
used it for something.

231
00:14:19,786 --> 00:14:21,415
H... half asleep?

232
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:26,925
For example, to make the room into a
locked room and stage an accident.

233
00:14:28,679 --> 00:14:32,770
Anyway, let's experiment.
See if it can really be done.

234
00:14:35,776 --> 00:14:38,532
First, the method for
setting the door lock.

235
00:14:38,782 --> 00:14:43,082
Thread the ribbon through the gap
between the door lock and the door,

236
00:14:43,375 --> 00:14:47,258
hold both ends of the ribbon,
step outside, and close the door.

237
00:14:48,009 --> 00:14:51,183
Then just pull both
ends of the ribbon.

238
00:14:51,266 --> 00:14:52,393
Good, Mitsuhiko.

239
00:14:52,477 --> 00:14:53,479
Roger.

240
00:14:54,189 --> 00:14:56,234
Pull it, please.
Got it.

241
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:02,455
I... it's locked.

242
00:15:02,914 --> 00:15:05,294
Next, the method for
setting the key lock.

243
00:15:05,378 --> 00:15:06,797
Open the door,

244
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:09,427
confirm the door lock is set,

245
00:15:09,844 --> 00:15:13,811
pull the ribbon out, and make
a knot in the middle of the ribbon.

246
00:15:14,688 --> 00:15:16,316
I made the knot.

247
00:15:16,692 --> 00:15:18,821
So that the knot catches,

248
00:15:18,904 --> 00:15:21,827
thread the ribbon through
the gap of the lock's thumb-turn.

249
00:15:22,161 --> 00:15:25,376
Run the end of the ribbon outside,
close the door,

250
00:15:26,085 --> 00:15:28,841
and pull the ribbon up
at an angle from outside...

251
00:15:31,596 --> 00:15:32,807
A... amazing.

252
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:35,354
The key really locked with a ribbon...
Hm?

253
00:15:35,855 --> 00:15:39,654
But unlike the door lock, can't you
not pull the ribbon back out?

254
00:15:39,946 --> 00:15:42,452
Hey, pull it with all your might.

255
00:15:42,744 --> 00:15:44,164
A... alright.

256
00:15:44,247 --> 00:15:47,754
But the door's shut, so the knot
catches and...

257
00:15:48,338 --> 00:15:51,762
That's strange. It should
have worked...

258
00:15:52,012 --> 00:15:54,768
Hmph. Just a child's
shallow scheme, after all.

259
00:15:55,644 --> 00:16:00,196
When you all came in here,
there was no ribbon like this, right?

260
00:16:00,279 --> 00:16:02,533
Right.
There was nothing.

261
00:16:02,825 --> 00:16:06,708
So the method to lock the key
with this ribbon is impossible.

262
00:16:06,792 --> 00:16:08,962
Yeah. The ribbon would
be left behind.

263
00:16:09,714 --> 00:16:13,137
If only someone could pull this ribbon
out from inside the room...

264
00:16:13,222 --> 00:16:15,476
and carry it off somewhere.

265
00:16:15,726 --> 00:16:17,730
Huh?
Someone, you say?

266
00:16:17,814 --> 00:16:19,526
The only one inside
was the victim...

267
00:16:19,609 --> 00:16:21,488
who's still unconscious, you know?

268
00:16:21,822 --> 00:16:23,575
Guess there's no helping it.

269
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:29,420
Look, over there.
You can do it.

270
00:16:30,172 --> 00:16:32,301
Keep the ribbon moving
like that.

271
00:16:32,385 --> 00:16:34,137
Got it.
Hm?

272
00:16:34,889 --> 00:16:36,643
(cat meowing)

273
00:16:41,903 --> 00:16:44,367
Ah, the... the cat...

274
00:16:44,450 --> 00:16:45,828
grabbed it and ran off.

275
00:16:45,911 --> 00:16:48,124
A... after it.
Y... yes.

276
00:16:51,381 --> 00:16:52,633
Behind the bookshelf?

277
00:16:54,178 --> 00:16:57,058
So this is the cat's
treasure hiding spot.

278
00:16:58,144 --> 00:17:00,774
Hm? Th... there it is.

279
00:17:00,858 --> 00:17:02,236
Different from the
earlier ribbon...

280
00:17:02,612 --> 00:17:04,365
another ribbon.

281
00:17:04,741 --> 00:17:08,165
It has a knot too,
so there's no mistake.

282
00:17:08,248 --> 00:17:09,250
Mm...

283
00:17:09,334 --> 00:17:13,258
The question is who set up
the trick with that ribbon.

284
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:17,391
I do think it was the work of someone
who knows cats well, though...

285
00:17:17,642 --> 00:17:22,318
Ah, well enough to know that the cat
wouldn't just carry the ribbon away,

286
00:17:22,401 --> 00:17:25,366
but would hide it somewhere.

287
00:17:25,866 --> 00:17:29,165
Then maybe it was the lady
with the glasses.

288
00:17:29,624 --> 00:17:33,340
Dai-chan was wagging his tail
when she held him.

289
00:17:33,590 --> 00:17:37,848
No, unlike dogs, when a cat wags
its tail, it means it's annoyed.

290
00:17:38,350 --> 00:17:42,065
Asou-san didn't know that, so
isn't she not very familiar with cats?

291
00:17:42,148 --> 00:17:43,568
Then Dai-chan was annoyed...

292
00:17:43,652 --> 00:17:46,908
because she was the bad person
who hurt his owner.

293
00:17:47,493 --> 00:17:50,666
If that were so, she wouldn't have
asked to hold him herself.

294
00:17:50,749 --> 00:17:52,837
She'd think she might
get scratched.

295
00:17:53,714 --> 00:17:59,308
The remaining two are Tsuyuguchi-san,
who was oddly concerned about saving electricity,

296
00:17:59,392 --> 00:18:01,771
and Urushiya-san, who picked up...

297
00:18:01,855 --> 00:18:04,485
what Genta-kun dropped
from his pocket,

298
00:18:04,902 --> 00:18:06,489
but both of those are habits,
or rather...

299
00:18:06,573 --> 00:18:09,370
Things they do without thinking.
Yes.

300
00:18:09,871 --> 00:18:13,962
But you know, back then, Genta
dropped a bandage,

301
00:18:14,046 --> 00:18:16,551
a handkerchief,
and a bottle cap,

302
00:18:16,634 --> 00:18:20,392
but the only thing he picked up
was the bottle cap, right?

303
00:18:21,186 --> 00:18:22,646
Now that you mention it,
that's true.

304
00:18:22,730 --> 00:18:24,358
But why?

305
00:18:24,442 --> 00:18:26,529
Then shall we test it?
Here.

306
00:18:28,157 --> 00:18:29,160
(cat meowing)

307
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,758
I see. This little guy loves
bottle caps too.

308
00:18:37,384 --> 00:18:39,889
I see. So the cat grabs it...

309
00:18:39,972 --> 00:18:43,188
and carries it off to its
treasure hiding spot,

310
00:18:43,271 --> 00:18:47,279
and they feared the ribbon used
in the trick would be discovered.

311
00:18:47,738 --> 00:18:52,206
Well, it seems to have been a spur-of-the-moment
crime using items at the scene,

312
00:18:52,832 --> 00:18:54,836
so if they weren't wearing gloves,

313
00:18:54,919 --> 00:18:57,216
fingerprints should come
off that ribbon.

314
00:18:57,591 --> 00:19:01,724
Alright, time to question
Urushiya-san again.

315
00:19:02,142 --> 00:19:06,484
Hey, what made you think
that novelist was suspicious?

316
00:19:06,568 --> 00:19:10,951
Was it because Dai-chan stood
his tail up at that person?

317
00:19:11,034 --> 00:19:14,040
That's a gesture they only
show to someone close...

318
00:19:14,124 --> 00:19:16,254
when they're happy
or feeling affectionate.

319
00:19:16,713 --> 00:19:21,264
Well, that's part of it, but the moment
he said someone opened the door...

320
00:19:21,347 --> 00:19:24,562
when he rang the
first-floor intercom,

321
00:19:24,645 --> 00:19:27,025
I had him pegged as the culprit.
Huh?

322
00:19:27,568 --> 00:19:32,661
If the culprit was the one who opened it,
then he was still inside the room at that point.

323
00:19:32,870 --> 00:19:35,584
He'd have to use the trick
at the entrance...

324
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:39,383
to create a locked room, so
summoning someone to the front...

325
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:42,681
of the door is just unthinkable.

326
00:19:45,019 --> 00:19:50,197
Indeed, I was the one who shoved him
and gave him those serious injuries.

327
00:19:50,781 --> 00:19:53,870
But to come up with a trick
like that on the spot...

328
00:19:53,954 --> 00:19:57,211
I once wrote a mystery
like that long ago.

329
00:19:57,711 --> 00:20:01,093
The truth is, I came today
to beg him for money.

330
00:20:01,594 --> 00:20:04,475
We were actually supposed
to meet tomorrow,

331
00:20:04,642 --> 00:20:09,067
but this morning he called and said
he'd prepared a nice gift,

332
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:13,243
so I couldn't sit still
and ended up coming today.

333
00:20:13,660 --> 00:20:15,455
But what I was handed...

334
00:20:15,539 --> 00:20:18,837
was a used pet carrier bag,

335
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:21,551
inside wrapping paper that
looked hastily done.

336
00:20:22,177 --> 00:20:25,392
And on top of that, inside
was that calico cat.

337
00:20:25,642 --> 00:20:31,111
Worse, he kept being coy, grinning,
saying he couldn't hand it over yet today.

338
00:20:31,404 --> 00:20:35,412
That cat was a stray I picked up
in the first place.

339
00:20:36,079 --> 00:20:38,418
So you were the one
who had it at first, mister?

340
00:20:38,877 --> 00:20:42,801
Yeah, just for about six
months when it was a kitten.

341
00:20:43,010 --> 00:20:46,934
His wife was down from losing a pet,
so I gave it to her.

342
00:20:47,478 --> 00:20:49,815
Well, giving it away
was the right call.

343
00:20:50,192 --> 00:20:53,155
After that, my novels suddenly
stopped selling,

344
00:20:53,239 --> 00:20:56,162
and I was in no position
to take care of a cat.

345
00:20:56,245 --> 00:21:00,212
His company, on the other hand,
seemed to be on the rise.

346
00:21:00,670 --> 00:21:02,925
And yet he tried to push...

347
00:21:03,008 --> 00:21:05,263
that stray cat off
on someone like me.

348
00:21:05,889 --> 00:21:08,895
Yes, the cat grabbed the
ribbon I'd untied...

349
00:21:08,978 --> 00:21:13,363
and dashed into the bedroom,
and while holding it, he said this:

350
00:21:13,822 --> 00:21:16,369
With this cat, you'll be fine.

351
00:21:16,452 --> 00:21:21,712
It was your cat to begin with, so
you're the more fitting owner.

352
00:21:24,552 --> 00:21:26,848
But Dai-chan is
an amazing cat.

353
00:21:27,266 --> 00:21:30,522
Male calico cats are a rare breed,
hardly ever born...

354
00:21:30,897 --> 00:21:32,734
They're super expensive,
you know.

355
00:21:32,943 --> 00:21:34,238
Huh?

356
00:21:34,697 --> 00:21:38,830
But the reason Masuko-san tried
to return the cat to you, mister,

357
00:21:38,913 --> 00:21:43,130
wasn't for money. It was because
that cat brings good fortune...

358
00:21:43,298 --> 00:21:45,802
a lucky beckoning cat,
wasn't it?

359
00:21:47,514 --> 00:21:53,526
♪~

360
00:23:01,495 --> 00:23:07,006
~♪

361
00:23:07,883 --> 00:23:12,476
That's great. Dai-chan's owner,
the mister, was discharged, right?

362
00:23:12,559 --> 00:23:15,022
Yes, and apparently
no lasting effects either.

363
00:23:15,273 --> 00:23:17,861
So what happened to that cat?

364
00:23:17,944 --> 00:23:21,202
In the end, Azusa-san from Poirot
ended up taking him in.

365
00:23:21,285 --> 00:23:22,788
(cat meowing)
Hm?

366
00:23:23,331 --> 00:23:24,792
Huh? Dai-chan?

367
00:23:25,168 --> 00:23:28,466
No way, did you become
a stray cat again?

368
00:23:28,549 --> 00:23:30,720
But isn't it kind of small?

369
00:23:30,804 --> 00:23:32,474
The pattern's identical, though.

370
00:23:33,184 --> 00:23:34,978
Come on, time to go home, Mugi.

371
00:23:35,563 --> 00:23:36,732
(cat meowing)

372
00:23:37,526 --> 00:23:38,986
Honestly, Grandma.

373
00:23:39,655 --> 00:23:42,118
You can't open the lid
of the carrier bag.

374
00:23:42,202 --> 00:23:45,250
Sorry, it just looked
so cramped.

375
00:23:45,333 --> 00:23:47,754
That old lady... I think she's...

376
00:23:48,381 --> 00:23:50,927
And they all lived
happily ever after?

377
00:23:52,764 --> 00:23:55,562
You sure about this?
I'm a peeping tom.

378
00:23:57,022 --> 00:23:58,943
Suzuki-san, you're
still here?

379
00:23:59,026 --> 00:24:02,451
The landlord told you to
hurry up and move out, didn't they?

380
00:24:03,034 --> 00:24:05,290
Hey, I've got a guest over.

381
00:24:05,373 --> 00:24:07,210
Please, stop it already,
Katsuko-san.

382
00:24:07,586 --> 00:24:09,130
Whoaaa.

383
00:24:09,631 --> 00:24:12,929
I... inside... Katsuko-san is...

384
00:24:14,140 --> 00:24:15,518
(three people screaming)

385
00:24:15,786 --> 00:24:17,186
Next Conan,

386
00:24:17,186 --> 00:24:20,986
"Share House Blind Spot".

387
00:24:36,486 --> 00:24:39,286
Next Conan's Hint:

388
00:24:39,286 --> 00:24:41,386
"Refrigerator".

389
00:24:41,541 --> 00:24:42,919
Leave the refrigerator to me.

390
00:24:43,002 --> 00:24:44,213
That makes no sense.

391
00:24:44,213 --> 00:24:46,386
After all, it's autumn. Genta's all for food, that's why.
